      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAKERO WARRIOR NZ (11) has had six-and-a-half weeks off since suffering atrial fibrillation but has been kept sharp since that outing with a minor placing at the trials. Came from a similar barrier to this when scoring two back at Melton and has only once missed a place in seven tries here, winning twice. BULLAPARK BENO (8) turned in a good effort at his latest run to come from this barrier to get home at Kilmore. Shouldn't spend a penny in the run and the sprint lane may come in handy. Could strike again. JAYS ALL THAT (5) raced wide and worked so was far from disgraced last start. Has won here before. With better luck he could be hard to stop. WATCH AND ACT (2) is heading the right way, improving last time out to come from this barrier and finish second at this venue.",
